es.utils.mapper.impl.object

Class ClassMapper<T,U>

  • java.lang.Object
    • es.utils.mapper.impl.MapperObject<T,U>
      • es.utils.mapper.impl.object.ClassMapper<T,U>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type of the origin object
    U - the type of the destination object

    public class ClassMapper<T,U>
extends MapperObject<T,U>
    This class customize the abstract class MapperObject creating a MapperObject that convert on object of type T into a U.
    Author:
    eschoysman
    See Also:
    MapperObject, DirectMapper, EnumMapper, ElementMapper

      • getMapping

        public <GETTER_OUT,SETTER_IN> Optional<ElementMapper<T,GETTER_OUT,SETTER_IN,U>> getMapping(String idNameFromTo)
        Returns the ElementMapper having the same idName as idNameFrom and idNameTo if present and the name is not ignored by the mapping.
        Calling this method is the same as calling getMapping(idNameFromTo,idNameFromTo)
        Type Parameters:
        GETTER_OUT - the type returned by the getter
        SETTER_IN - the type required by the setter
        Parameters:
        idNameFromTo - the name identifier of the getter and setter associated to the ElementMapper to return
        Returns:
        The ElementMapper if present and idNameFromTo is not ignored

      • getMapping

        public <GETTER_OUT,SETTER_IN> Optional<ElementMapper<T,GETTER_OUT,SETTER_IN,U>> getMapping(String idNameFrom,
                                                                                           String idNameTo)
        Returns the ElementMapper between the names idNameFrom and idNameTo if present and both names are not ignored by the mapping
        Type Parameters:
        GETTER_OUT - the type returned by the getter
        SETTER_IN - the type required by the setter
        Parameters:
        idNameFrom - the name identifier of the setter associated to the ElementMapper to return
        idNameTo - the name identifier of the getter associated to the ElementMapper to return
        Returns:
        The ElementMapper if present and from and to are not ignored
